&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;STRONG Pilates- Campus Brand Ambassador&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About STRONG&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are STRONG, a Pilates-inspired, cardio-infused experience built for the modern athlete. Low impact, high intensity, all power.&amp;nbsp;Born in Australia and now expanding rapidly across the U.S., STRONG is the evolution of Pilates. Our signature&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;ROW. RIDE. REFORM.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;classes fuse Pilates precision with heart-pumping cardio, delivered on our world-first Rowformer and Bikeformer machines — all in a powerful 45-minute full-body session designed to strengthen, sculpt, and perform. With 100+ studios opening nationwide, including New York, Chicago, Boston, Los Angeles, Dallas, Houston, and beyond, STRONG is transforming the fitness landscape one studio at a time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a STRONG Pilates Campus Ambassador, you are more than a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;167&quot; data-end=&quot;176&quot;&gt;voic&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;e.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;You are the movement on campus. You’ll bring the STRONG experience directly into your university community, building authentic connections, generating buzz, and turning curiosity into committed members. Your mission is to spark awareness, drive student traffic to the studio, and cultivate a loyal campus community that doesn’t just try STRONG, they stay STRONG. This role is designed for natural connectors and culture-shapers — students who are passionate about fitness, energized by social engagement, and excited to introduce their peers to something powerful, elevated, and results-driven.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Brand Awareness &amp;amp; On-Campus Presence&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a confident and authentic voice for STRONG Pilates within your university community&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create visibility for the brand by actively engaging peers, student organizations, and campus events&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generate excitement around STRONG studios, class formats, and special programs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate what sets STRONG apart — from the workout experience to the results-driven community&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Spark conversations that turn curiosity into studio visits and long-term membership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Member Growth &amp;amp; Retention Support&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Encourage classmates to try STRONG and continue returning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support participation in studio challenges, programs, and community initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help nurture long-term loyalty beyond one-time visits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Community Building&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a connector between your campus and STRONG&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build relationships with student groups, athletics, wellness programs, and campus leaders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support and participate in studio events when possible&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Social Media &amp;amp; Digital Promotion&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Share STRONG content authentically&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create campus-relevant content such as stories, reels, testimonials, and invitations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Promote offers, challenges, and studio updates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Encourage others to tag and share their STRONG experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Outreach &amp;amp; Partnerships&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help identify student partnership and collaboration opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support pop-ups, student nights, collaborations, and giveaways&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Communication &amp;amp; Reporting&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT STRONG&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are STRONG – A Pilates-inspired, cardio-infused, and designed for a full-body workout that is low-impact and high-intensity. Our diverse classes, including&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;ROW&lt;/strong&gt;,&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;RIDE&lt;/strong&gt;, and&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;REFORM&lt;/strong&gt;, are designed to help clients maximize their performance and achieve their fitness goals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE ROLE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;STRONG CLASSES:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver STRONG Pilates classes based on set schedule&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Give clients personal attention during class, ensure that your cueing is clear, precise and easy to follow, and ensure clients are using correct form at all times&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Know client’s injuries before class so that you can modify where need be&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inspire and promote an energetic environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Balance teaching, changing lights and music during class all while staying on top of your timing and programming for the day&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure each client is introduced to the Rowformer and Bikeformer prior to class&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;COMMUNITY:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proudly represent your STRONG studio at all times&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Welcome clients by name&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Always know when it’s a client’s first class and celebrate milestones&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enthusiastic and supportive attitude towards clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to develop STRONG relationships with clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continue to build the community culture of STRONG&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in the sale of memberships, merchandise and other offerings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;STUDIO:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain upkeep of the studio in-between classes including cleaning equipment, reformer maintenance, and restrooms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with washing/soaking/rolling of eucalyptus towels when requested&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take pride in the studio like it is your own&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ADMIN:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle client interactions from walk ins, phone and email where needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Assist in generating and converting membership sales&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SKILLS &amp;amp; EXPERIENCE:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to multitask&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent presentation and verbal skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness to work flexible hours&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to motivate clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Customer service oriented&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-motivated&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passion, enthusiasm, and genuine motivation towards wanting to improve the lives of others&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent attention to detail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledgeable with anatomy and physiology of the body, standard movement patterns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;QUALIFICATIONS:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6+ months of group fitness teaching experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reliable means of mobility for travel to studio location&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;STRONG Academy certification (Provided by STRONG)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Certified Personal Trainer or Pilates certification from a recognized organization&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CPR and AED certification obtained through in-person training is required&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CULTURE &amp;amp; BENEFITS:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive Compensation and Commission Eligibility&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible Work Schedule&l

